            </me>
            models the mass of radioactive atoms in a substance (in \si{\milli\gram}) <m>t</m> years after the sample was established. Use a graphing calculator to approximate the half-life for the given values of <m>Q_0</m> and <m>k</m>. State 
            your answers correctly to 2 decimal places.
            \begin{multicols}{2}
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                <m>Q_0=4</m>, <m>k=-0.0001</m>
