<title>Continuous growth rate</title>
<statement>
            For each of the exponential functions defined by the formulas below, find the continuous growth rate and the growth rate.
            \begin{multicols}{3}
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                <m>f(t) = e^t</m>
              </statement>
              <solution>
                <p>
                  <m>e^t\approx 2.7182818^t</m>, so <m>f</m> has continuous growth rate 1 and growth rate about 1.7182818.
                </p>
              </solution>
            </exercise>
