<title>True or false</title>
<statement>
            Answer the following questions as True or False; if you believe the answer 
            to be False, provide justification that supports your answer.
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                Linear functions are concave down.
              </statement>
              <solution>
                <p>
                  False; linear functions are neither concave up nor concave down.
                </p>
              </solution>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                Linear functions are concave up.
              </statement>
              <solution>
                <p>
                  False; linear functions are neither concave up nor concave down.
                </p>
              </solution>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                It is possible to write a linear function that has a slope of <m>2</m>.
              </statement>
              <solution>
                <p>
                  True.
                </p>
              </solution>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
              <statement>
                It is possible to write an exponential function that has a slope of <m>2</m>.
              </statement>
              <solution>
